{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]He’s a rootin’ tootin’ Santa Claus
Ridin’ reindeer through the [D7]sky
With his spurs a-jinglin’ janglin’ 
And his lasso swinging [G]high
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
He’s a rootin’ tootin’ Santa Claus
Saddle bags all packed with [D7]toys
Through the chimney he will bring them all
To the dreaming girls and [G]boys
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Get [C]along little reindeer get along 
[G]Cover all the range tonight
It’s a [A7]long long trail an all night trail
But [D7]you can bet your boots that Santa won’t fail
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
